  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Protection, Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items interventions benefiting drought affected populations (IDPs and vulnerable host communities) in Galmudug and South West States</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this $1.5m UNHCR project is to identify and respond to protection concerns, on the one hand, and provide emergency shelter and non-food items, on the other hand. UNHCR, in partnership with Norwegian Refugee Council, will deploy protection monitors who will conduct over 200 interviews and focus group discussions with key informants and share key messages on prevention and access to services with 30,000 people. In addition, UNHCR and its partners will identify 2,500 persons with specific needs and provide the required assistive devices as well as ensure that 1,000 persons can access legal, psychosocial and medical services. Five hundred families at risk of eviction will be provided with information, counselling and legal aid. In addition, UNHCR will distribute 2,350 shelter kits and 2,000 kits with non-food items. In total, UNHCR will reach 30,000 people (incl. 7,497 women and 7,803 girls) through the protection component and 19,575 people (incl. 3,349 women and 7,810 girls) through the shelter and non-food items component.</narrative>
  </description>
